algorithm_technique: Digit DP with precomputed counts and careful boundary handling
problem_summary_simple: Count numbers up to n that look different when rotated 180 degrees.
problem_summary_technical: Digit DP to count numbers with valid digits, subtracting unconfusing numbers based on length and prefix.
key_insights: The core idea is to count all numbers formed by valid digits and subtract those that are not confusing.
Digit DP is suitable for counting numbers within a range based on digit properties.
Careful handling of leading zeros and the middle digit for odd-length numbers is crucial.
